Feb 2020 > November 2020

Look how much my puppy grew in those short months. Puppy months are faster than human months!

One of the monthly themes in my new p52 course through @hellostoryteller is “Room by Room” where each week that month we focus on a different room in your home. 

You guessed it, one week is all about the BATHROOM!

Weird, right? Haha! Maybe! But some of my favorite images are taken in a bathroom. Do you avoid this room when documenting your days?

If you’d be interested in themes and weekly prompts like this, join my waitlist. The link is in my bio.

2019 > 2020 > 2022

Recreating or re-imagining images is one of my favorite things. These mirror self portraits are especially sentimental to me. 

Do you have images you like to recreate?

One of the monthly exercises in my new p52 course through @hellostoryteller is to take an old image and recreate it. Then study both images to see the differences — composition, use of light, etc. 

This type of exercise is great in pinpointing our strengths & weaknesses, which is a great catalyst for growth. 

If this type of exercise appeals to you, you’ll love my course! It’s full of monthly theme exercises like this. Plus weekly prompt exercises designed to get you out shooting. 

Join my waitlist for updates. Link in my bio.

I like to take my kids on individual dates. It’s never anything overly special. Playing cards at a restaurant. Or going to get ice cream. But I cherish the one-on-one time so much. It was this girl’s turn over the weekend. We went to our favorite sandwich place and played Dominoes. Then we had a sleepover in my bed while watching Moana. We had the whole king size bed to ourselves (husband was kicked out), but she curled up as close to me as she could. That’s how she got her nickname Barnacle Baby. 

I’m distinctly aware one day my kids won’t be as eager to go on dates with me, so I’m going to eat it up now while I can. 

……………………………………………

9 | Directional Light

Tomorrow I fly to California for the Hello Storyteller Admin Retreat and I. Can’t. Wait!!

We’ve been planning this thing for months. It’ll be a mix of business (all day branding shoot + meeting of the minds) with pleasure (sight seeing, girl time, fun photo sessions + more girl time).

It’s a funny thing—working from home for an online photography community. I talk to my coworkers all day long as if we were in an office setting, but we never get to actually see each other. I look forward to these admin retreats every year so we can be face to face.

I chopped my hair off yesterday because I needed a change. I showed up in head to toe yellow for my appointment and my hair lady was like, is yellow your favorite color? So, yeah, some things don’t change — like my love for yellow & dandelions, and my new yellow chucks — but now my hair is short.
